Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
highlight_timing_report(25.10)                  highlight_timing_report(25.10)

Name
       highlight_timing_report

Syntax
        highlight_timing_report

       [-help]

       [-append]

       [-color_index <integer>]

       [-file <filename> ]

       [-noarrow]

       [-path <path_number >| -all]

       This  command  enables  you  to highlight a specific number of paths in
       Global Timing Debug through user interface.  The  input  timing  report
       must  be in a machine readable format that is understood by Global Tim-
       ing Debug. For more information, see the Debugging Timing Results chap-
       ter of the Innovus User Guide document.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each highlight_timing_report parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man highlight_timing_report

       -all   Highlights all the path in the Global Timing Debug  through  the
              user interface.

       -append
              Appends a path to the current highlight.

       -color_index <integer>
              Specifies the path's color index on a scale of 1 to 8.

       -file <filename>
              Reads  the  machine readable file and also specifies the name of
              the file. The option is of type string and is optional.

       -noarrow
              Removes the highlighted arrow. The option is of type boolean and
              optional.

       -path <path_number>
              Specifies the number of the path. The option is of  type  string
              and  required.  It  is  recommended to use positive integers for
              specifying the <path_number>.

Example
       The following commands generate the worst 1000 paths to a machine read-
       able report, and then highlight the top five paths in Global Timing De-
       bug:

       report_timing -machine_readable -max_points 1000 > foo.mtarpt

       load_timing_debug_report foo.mtarpt

       highlight_timing_report -file foo.mtarpt -path "1 2 3 4 5" -noarrow

Related Information
       The Debugging Timing Results chapter of the Innovus  User  Guide  docu-
       ment.

